Key Match Events: The Orioles took a 5-3 loss to the Giants at Camden Yards.
The O's scored a pair in the third on an RBI double by James McCann and an RBI groundout from Cedric Mullins.
Ryan O'Hearn hit a two-out RBI double on the first pitch delivered by left-hander Erik Miller.
The bases became loaded when Heston Kjerstad was hit by a pitch with two outs, but Colton Cowser flied out to left to end the inning.
Pre-Game Insights: Analysts predicted a close game between the two rival teams.
Post-Match Reflections: Brandon Hyde said he thought the encouraging thing with tonight's game a little bit is that he thought that our at-bats were better.
Colton Cowser said that momentum is something that just kind of happens. You can't really force it, because that's when guys start pressing and you struggle even more.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Orioles lost for the ninth time in 12 games.
Their deficit in the American League East is a season-high five games behind the first-place Yankees.
They're clinging to the top spot in the AL Wild Card standings.
Others: Injury reinforcements Jordan Westburg and Ramón Urías will begin rehab assignments at Triple-A Norfolk on Thursday.
The Orioles have scored three or fewer runs in 10 of its past 12 games, plating 24 total runs over that span.
